column7: Dell XPS 8940 Special Edition Tower Desktop ComputerOperating SystemGet the best combination of Windows features you know and new improvements you’ll love.Power for everything you doStay in the flow with a new 11th Gen Intel Core processor-powered XPS desktop that handles your creative projects with ease, like editing photos and videos,so they’re ready to share in a flash. Immerse yourself in your favorite show, the latest popular game, or a new creative project – and never think twice about your PC’s ability to keep up.Designed with you in mind, 11th Gen InteI Core desktop processors give you the performance you’ve always wanted, for everything you do.Keep your coolAll of the decisions made through the design process for the Desktop were made purposefully to maximize performance and airflow. Starting with the use afront bezel which allows the airflow path to draw cool air from front to back over graphics cards and CPU, the power supply unit and the M.2 SSD storage. Finally, theopen architecture layout means nothing is sitting on top of the CPU and GPU, limiting airflow.Regulated coolingOur engineers designed this system to include voltage regulator cooling with select processors to ensure system optimal performance by maintainingadequate airflow over the VR components. They also selected an optimal location for the placement of the M.2 SSD to maximize performance and rigorous, proprietarytesting ensures that all system components are kept cool, even under the most intensive loads.Designed to stay quietThe XPS Desktop was designed to blend into your environment, whether that be a family room, office or kitchen, you can be assured your desktop will stayquiet, even when it’s performing at its highest. The XPS Desktop uses high RPM fans, with a maximum system fan speed of 4500 rpm to more efficiently cool.

column7: Dell OptiPlex 5080 SFF Small Form Factor Desktop ComputerTake advantage of enterprise-level performance and easy system manageability in a small form factorwith the OptiPlex 5080 SFF Desktop Computer from Dell. Designed to handle daily workloads, thissmall-form-factor desktop features a 10th Gen Intel Core CPU and 2933MHz DDR4 RAM for powerfulprocessing. Additionally, the integrated Intel UHD 630 Graphics supports multiple monitors, providingample screen space. Silicon-level security measures like a TPM chip and a chassis-intrusion alarm allowyou to maintain system integrity. Support for Kensington and 3rd party locks allows for securedeployment and easy remote management of the OS, firmware, and apps translates to less strain onIT and unified endpoints for your workforce.
